# Vault (knowledge paths)

Consult `vault_storage.md` in this framework for the full lifecycle table and templates.

## Moves (after user approval)

- Inbox file in `inbox/`: after the summary is added at the top and topics are updated, move the file to `processed-inbox/`. After that move, reset `inbox/notes.md` to empty (standing scratch file for the next notes).
- Archive: only move a topic from `topics/` to `archived-topics/` when the user agrees it is obsolete.

## Topic file sections (active topics in `topics/`)

Use the structure in `vault_storage.md` (Current State, Decisions, Open Questions, Action Items, Key People, References).

## Reference knowledge (`knowledge/*.md` except `glossary.md`)

Stable reference articles -- no required template or durable-topic lifecycle sections. Freeform.

## Glossary (`knowledge/glossary.md`)

Reserved term index; always read on orient/parse when working under the knowledge root. See `vault_storage.md` section on glossary. Not a durable topic.

## Summary section (at the top of inbox files)

Match the summary section template in `vault_storage.md` (Date processed, Topics links, Key Points, Decisions, Action Items). When an action item remains active beyond processing, mirror it into the relevant topic file as well.
